description:
This animations is based on a real Moon picture, how It was made :

1) Many years ago I took a picture of the Moon using a telescope;
2) Read the picture file and reduce its resolution by a factor of 10 - then you have the coordinates ; 
3) Refine the coordinates choosing a channel and the intensity level, in this case only the blue channel and certain levels of brightness (this is a trial and error process) - to set the best visual look ;
4) Now to each point assign an Archimedean spiral, with size related to light intensity, but with random direction and initial position of turning ;
5) Loop the rotations (30 frames).


All process was done in Python 3 using Matplolib, Numpy, Pillow and Random libraries.
